Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of decision trees, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and speech recognition tasks, suggesting that cs.CL (Computation and Language) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with tabular data, which is a type of structured data, indicating that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may also be a relevant sub-category.
